{"patient_id": "152", "personal_information": {"name": "", "gender": "Female", "dob": "1967-06-09", "age": 58}, "vitals": {}, "lab_results": [], "radiology_reports": [{"cpt_id": "1000000000070488", "cpt_name": "C.T. Chest High Resolution  (HR Chest)", "technique": "Multiple axial sections were taken through chest without I.V contrast injection (HRCT protocol).", "result": "Areas of air trapping showing fine nodularity, forming tree-in-bud pattern in the apico-posterior segment of the left upper lobe in the apical segment of the left lower lobe and apical segment of the right lower lobe. Fine reticular changes with mild traction bronchiectasis is noted in the basal segments more on right side, suggestive of interstitial lung disease. No definite area of consolidation. No cavitatory lesion. Normal trachea and major airway. No pleural effusion seen on either side. 

