{"patient_id": "153", "personal_information": {"name": "", "gender": "Male", "dob": "1960-08-19", "age": 65}, "vitals": {}, "lab_results": [], "radiology_reports": [{"cpt_id": "1000000000070488", "cpt_name": "C.T. Chest High Resolution  (HR Chest)", "technique": "Multiple axial sections were taken through chest without I.V contrast injection (HRCT protocol).", "result": "Extensive areas of ground glass opacification in bilateral lung fields. Interlobular septal and intralobular interstitial thickening forming reticular pattern noted in bilateral lung fields more marked in bilateral lower lobes with evidence of traction bronchiectasis. Multiple small air containing cysts and honeycombing noted in bilateral peri bronchovascular and posterior basal regions. Normal trachea and major airway. No pleural effusion seen on either side. 

Images of mediastinal window show prominent prevascular and aortopulmonary lymphnodes. Mildly enlarged precarinal (measuring 13.0 mm), para tracheal (10.8 mm), and aortopulmonary (14.0 mm) lymphnodes containing foci of calcification. A few sections through upper abdomen are unremarkable. No significant skeletal abnormality.", "conclusion": "Ground glass opacification noted bilaterally. Extensive reticular changes with evidence of traction bronchiectasis in bilateral lung fields more marked in bilateral lower lobes. Honeycombing noted in bilateral posterior basal region. Features are suggestive of interstitial lung disease (NSIP pattern). Clinical and lab correlation suggested for further evaluation. 

