{"patient_id": "17", "personal_information": {"name": "", "gender": "Female", "dob": "1948-02-06", "age": 78}, "vitals": {}, "lab_results": [], "radiology_reports": [{"cpt_id": "1000000000070488", "cpt_name": "C.T. Chest High Resolution  (HR Chest)", "technique": "Multiple axial sections were taken through chest without I.V contrast injection (HRCT protocol).", "result": "Air trapping is noted in bilateral lung fields. Patchy areas of ground glass opacification are present bilaterally in the lung fields. Few tiny air containing cysts noted in the right middle lobe and left upper lobe. Calcified granuloma measuring 6.9 x 7.3 mm noted in the right lower lobe. A pleural nodule measuring 5.5 x 3.5 mm noted in the right horizontal fissure. Smooth interlobular septal thickening noted in bilateral lung fields, more marked in lower lobes with increase vessels to bronchus ratio. Suggestion of cardiomegaly.  No infiltration or consolidation identified in either lung field. No evidence of bronchiectasis. Normal trachea and major airway. No pleural effusion seen on either side. Subsegmental atelectasis is noted in right middle lobe. 

Images of mediastinal window show no definite mediastinal lymphadenopathy or mass. Large sliding hiatal hernia. Atherosclerotic plaques noted in the arch of aorta. A few sections through upper abdomen are unremarkable. Osteopenia of visualized skeleton.", "conclusion": "Air trapping with ground glass opacification noted in bilateral lung fields. Air containing cysts noted in right middle lobe and left upper lobe. Smooth interlobular septal thickening noted in bilateral lung fields, more marked in bilateral lower lobes with increased vessels to bronchus ratio. Suggestion of cardiomegaly. Features are concerning for interstitial pulmonary edema. Echocardiography would be helpful for further evaluation. Large hiatal hernia. 

