{"patient_id": "185", "personal_information": {"name": "", "gender": "Male", "dob": "1980-06-12", "age": 45}, "vitals": {}, "lab_results": [], "radiology_reports": [{"cpt_id": "1000000000073202", "cpt_name": "C.T. Sinus without Contrast", "technique": "Multiple axial sections were taken through the region of paranasal sinuses without IV contrast injection with sagittal and coronal reconstruction images.", "result": "There is complete opacification of the left maxillary sinus with widening of the sinus ostium and soft tissue densities extending into the left sided nasal cavity, almost completely filing the left ethmoidal air cells and left sided frontal sinus. Sphenoid sinus appears unremarkable. Internal hyperdensities within soft tissue densities are concerning for superadded fungal infection. 

There is obliteration of the posterior nares on left side, however nasopharynx appear unremarkable. Extreme thinning / erosion of the lamina papyracea on left side.", "conclusion": "CT features are suggestive of sinonasal polyposis with superadded fungal infection. Extreme thinning / erosion of the lamina papyracea on left side.

