{"patient_id": "186", "personal_information": {"name": "", "gender": "Female", "dob": "1964-11-18", "age": 61}, "vitals": {}, "lab_results": [], "radiology_reports": [{"cpt_id": "1000000000070488", "cpt_name": "C.T. Chest High Resolution  (HR Chest)", "technique": "Multiple axial sections were taken through chest without I.V contrast injection (HRCT protocol).", "result": "Small focal areas of pleural thickening on right side. Subsegmental atelectasis and minimal bronchiectasis in left upper lobe inferior lingular segment. Minimal reticular changes in left lower lobe. Focal sub segment atelectasis is identified in right upper lobe subpleural location. No definite infiltration or consolidation on either side. No nodularity. Normal trachea and major airway. No pleural effusion seen on either side. 

Images of mediastinal window show no definite mediastinal lymphadenopathy or mass. Small atherosclerotic calcification of coronary arteries. Suggestion of small hypodense nodule in left lobe of thyroid, requires correlation with ultrasound thyroid. A few sections through upper abdomen show a tiny right renal calculus. Visualized skeleton shows mild degenerative changes and mild osteopenia.", "conclusion": "Known case of gluteal region sarcoma. No definite area of consolidation or infiltration. No evidence of pulmonary metastasis. Sub segment atelectasis in bilateral upper lobes can be due to subtle inflammatory process. 

