{"patient_id": "193", "personal_information": {"name": "", "gender": "Female", "dob": "1958-11-11", "age": 67}, "vitals": {}, "lab_results": [], "radiology_reports": [{"cpt_id": "1000000000070488", "cpt_name": "C.T. Chest High Resolution  (HR Chest)", "technique": "Multiple axial sections were taken through chest without I.V contrast injection (HRCT protocol).", "result": "Ground glass opacification bilaterally in the lung fields, predominantly in the dependent lung parenchyma on either side with mild smooth interlobular septal thickening in the basal regions bilaterally. NO definite area of consolidation. No nodularity or bronchiectasis. Normal trachea and major airway. No pleural effusion seen on either side. 
