{"patient_id": "204", "personal_information": {"name": "", "gender": "Female", "dob": "1965-01-25", "age": 61}, "vitals": {}, "lab_results": [], "radiology_reports": [{"cpt_id": "1000000000070488", "cpt_name": "C.T. Chest High Resolution  (HR Chest)", "technique": "Multiple axial sections were taken through chest without I.V contrast injection (HRCT protocol).", "result": "Patch areas of ground glass opacification bilaterally in the lung fields with smooth interlobular septal thickness. No definite area of consolidation. No bronchiectasis. No nodularity. No evidence of bronchiectasis. Normal trachea and major airway. No pleural effusion seen on either side. Grossly enlarged heart. Echocardiographic correlation suggested for further evaluation. 

Images of mediastinal window show a few prominent para-tracheal and pre-vascular lymphnodes. No definite mediastinum mass. A fluid density just anterior to the anterior surface of the liver measuring approximately 54 x 26 mm in the axial plane. Liver shows mildly nodular surface. Please correlate clinically and with lab findings to rule out chronic liver disease. No significant skeletal abnormality.", "conclusion": "Patchy areas of ground glass opacification with mild smooth interlobular septal thickening and gross cardiomegaly are concerning for changes of pulmonary edema. Clinical and echocardiographic correlation advised. Fluid density just anterior to anterior surface of the liver, needs ultrasound correlation. Nodular surface of the liver. Please correlate clinically and with lab findings, to rule out chronic liver disease. 

